cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is primarily focused on face detection using facial segments and proposes two algorithms, one of which is based on deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of weak boosted classifiers and data augmentation, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also deals with mobile face datasets, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the proposed algorithms to occlusion, which is a common problem in computer security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category as well.
